# Adaptive RAG Research Project — Progress Report

## 🎯 What Was the Original Agenda?

**Thesis**: *"Similarity score distributions are structured, query-dependent signals. We characterize their shape taxonomy, use them for adaptive retrieval, and show confidence scores predict answer quality without ground truth."*

In plain English: **Build a smarter RAG system** that looks at *how* similarity scores are distributed (not just the top score) to decide how many documents to retrieve, what kind of answer to generate, and how confident it should be — all without needing human-labeled ground truth.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Yes, this is turning into a research paper.** The 16-week plan in [task.md.resolved](file:///d:/Programming/AI/RAG/food_domain_rag/task.md.resolved) explicitly has **Phase 4 (Weeks 13–16): Paper Writing**, with sections ordered 3→4→5→2→1→Abstract. The entire project is structured as academic research.

