## 🏗 How Everything Was Built (The Process)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[5000 Yelp Reviews] -->|ingest.py| B[8876 Chunks in FAISS]
    B -->|rag_query.py| C[Retrieve K=20 with scores]
    C -->|score_logger.py| D[100 Score Curves → CSV/JSON]
    D -->|analyze_curves.py| E[Kurtosis/Entropy/Slope Features]
    E --> F[curve_features.json + Plots]
    
    G[generate_queries.py] -->|Mistral 7B| H[300 Research Queries]
    H -->|filter_queries.py| I[Filtered Query Set]
```

1. **Ingestion**: Yelp reviews loaded, chunked (512/100, sentence-aware), embedded with BGE-base-en-v1.5 (normalized, CUDA), stored in FAISS
2. **Retrieval**: Every query retrieves K=20 candidates, FAISS L2 distances converted to cosine similarity via `cos_sim = 1 - L2²/2`
3. **Score Logging**: Full 20-score vector saved for every query (both CSV for quick analysis, JSON for full detail including LLM response)
4. **Feature Extraction**: Per-curve kurtosis, entropy, slope, range, top-1 dominance, bimodality coefficient
5. **Query Generation**: Mistral 7B generates 300 queries (75 per intent) from Yelp review context, with deduplication and filtering

